";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"wp-recaptcha\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"http://www.snilesh.com/?p=2663\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:884:\"<p>The Post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.snilesh.com/wordpress-comment-spam-filter-plugins/\">wordpress comment spam filter plugins</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.snilesh.com\">Nilesh Shiragave</a></p><div style=\"display:block; clear:both;\"><img width=\"400\" height=\"193\" src=\"http://www.snilesh.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/wordpress-comment-spam-filter-plugins-400x193.png\" class=\"attachment-medium wp-post-image\" alt=\"wordpress comment spam filter plugins\" style=\"float:right; margin:0 0 10px 10px;\" /></div><p>Whether you have a small wordpress website or you have a very big corporate website , You have to protect your blog posts against spam. WordPress plugins need to be installed to protect against spam. There are huge number or anti spam wordpress plugins available on wordpress.org plugin repository. In this post we will list [&#8230;]</p> \";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Nilesh Shiragave\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4422:\"<p>The Post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.snilesh.com/wordpress-comment-spam-filter-plugins/\">wordpress comment spam filter plugins</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.snilesh.com\">Nilesh Shiragave</a></p><div style=\"display:block; clear:both;\"><img width=\"400\" height=\"193\" src=\"http://www.snilesh.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/wordpress-comment-spam-filter-plugins-400x193.png\" class=\"attachment-medium wp-post-image\" alt=\"wordpress comment spam filter plugins\" style=\"float:right; margin:0 0 10px 10px;\" /></div><p>Whether you have a small wordpress website or you have a very big corporate website , You have to protect your blog posts against spam. WordPress plugins need to be installed to protect against spam. There are huge number or anti spam wordpress plugins available on wordpress.org plugin repository. In this post we will list best anti spam wordpress plugins.</p><h2>Best Anti-Smap WordPress Plugins</h2><h3>1]Akismet</h3><p>Akismet is best free wordpress plugin available on wordpress.org website created by automatic developers who created wordpress. Akismet is launched in 2005, which keeps track of all comments,trackbacks and pingbacks using a complex filtering engine on your wordpress blog.</p><p>Akismet plugin comes with wordpress script or you have to download that from Akismet Plugin. Akismet requires a <a href=\"http://akismet.com/get/\" title=\"Akismet API key\" target=\"_blank\">Akismet.com API key</a> but once you install plugin and configure using API key then you can literally forget the about this plugin. It will start protecting your blog from spam comments.<br /> <a class=\"btn btn-custom  \" href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/spam-free-wordpress/\" target=\"\" >Download Akismet</a><h3>2] WP-reCAPTCHA</h3><p><a href=\"http://recaptcha.net/\" title=\"reCaptcha\" target=\"_blank\">reCAPTCHA</a> is an anti-spam method originating from Carnegie Mellon University, then acquired by Google which uses CAPTCHAs in a genius way. reCAPTCHA uses a different approach than traditional randomly generated useless characters.</p><p>Wp-reCAPTCHA integrates reCAPTCHA anti-spam methods inside a wordpress plugin which helps protecting wordpress comments,trackbacks and pingbacks from spam.</p><p>Wp-reCAPTCHA requires a API Key which you can get here. Install Wp-reCAPTCHA plugin and configure that using key and forget about spams.<br /> <a class=\"btn btn-custom  \" href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-recaptcha/\" target=\"\" >Download WP-reCaptcha</a><h3>3] Spam Stopper</h3><p><a href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/spam-stopper/\" title=\"Spam Stopper Plugin\" target=\"_blank\">Spam Stopper plugin</a> is used to keep spammer robots from posting on your blog, reducing the space taken by spam messages in the database, and preventing your blog from being a spam magnet. You can ask simple questions on your wordpress blog , e.g. Is the sky Green? NO!. Doing this will stop stupid bots from being able to post.<br /> <a class=\"btn btn-custom  \" href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/spam-stopper/\" target=\"\" >Download Spam Stopper Plugin</a><h3>4] Growmap Anti Spambot Plugin</h3><p><a href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/growmap-anti-spambot-plugin/\" title=\"Growmap anti Spam\" target=\"_blank\">Growmap Anti Spambot Plugin</a> add a client side generated checkbox on your websites comment form asking your users to confirm that they are not a spammer or a bot. It is a lot less trouble to click a box than it is to enter a captcha and because the box is genereated via client side javascript that bots cannot see, it should stop 99% of all automated spam bots.<br /> <a class=\"btn btn-custom  \" href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/growmap-anti-spambot-plugin/\" target=\"\" >Download Growmap</a><h3>5] SPAM Free WordPress</h3><p><a href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/spam-free-wordpress/\" title=\"SPAM free wordpress plugin\" target=\"_blank\">Spam Free WordPress</a> is a anti-spam wordpress plugin that can help to block automated comment spam. The protection is great for some small blogs, but other blogs that are targeted by spammers need something more powerful.</p><p>That’s it, Article completes all the top anti spam wordpress plugin list. You have to use any one plugin to protect from spams. Use any one plugin which suits your wordpress blog .<br /> <a class=\"btn btn-custom  \" href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/spam-free-wordpress/\" target=\"\" >Download SPAM free WordPress</a> \";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"http://www.snilesh.com/wordpress-comment-spam-filter-plugins/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"hourly\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"updateFrequency\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";s:4:\"href\";s:35:\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/snilesh\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:2:{s:3:\"rel\";s:3:\"hub\";s:4:\"href\";s:32:\"http://pubsubhubbub.appspot.com/\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/f